data.title: How Much It REALLY Costs to Book Your Favorite Band
data.meta_description: Since 1999 Lambgoat has been bringing you the latest in heavy metal and hardcore. Find news, new music, tour dates, release dates, reviews, interviews, and a message board.
data.text:
Expenses for booking popular acts can differ wildly, influenced by many factors including the band's popularity and the group's availability. As such, we have compiled a detailed list of booking fees to compare various bands and artists' rates for the year 2024. This list has been meticulously sourced from Celebrity Talent International, the same resource we have used in the past to compile a list of booking fees ten years ago. This website is long-standing in the industry, with direct connections to talent management agencies. This makes it a decent source, though there are some obvious inaccuracies, so take this list with a grain of salt.

When it comes to who's asking what for music booking fees in 2024, several notable bands stand out for their large demands. As I Lay Dying reportedly seeks $450,000, whereas Avenged Sevenfold commands a fee of $800,000+, while the legendary Iron Maiden has a booking fee surpassing $2,000,000. In the realm of pop, icons like Mariah Carey and Britney Spears are listed with fees of $1,000,000+ each. Additionally, legendary groups such as The Eagles and Queen (with Adam Lambert presumably) are also in the high fee bracket, with fees around $2,000,000.

Remember, these amounts are not what a band gets for playing a show amidst a tour, but rather what they might ask for to fly into some random city for a one-off performance. Booking fees can then often be negotiated from there.
